Put the Parmesan and garlic in the bowl of a food processor and pulse until the consistency of coarse breadcrumbs. Add the drained artichokes, preserved lemon and parsley and whizz again.Gradually add the olive oil in a steady stream until the mixture reaches a dippable consistency (you might not need all the oil). Season to taste with lemon juice, salt and freshly ground black pepper. Spoon into a bowl and sprinkle with extra parsley.